# UI/UX Design Principles

## Visual Hierarchy
- Use font size, weight, and spacing to create clear information hierarchy
- Main content should be the focal point of each screen
- Use consistent spacing between elements (8px, 16px, 24px, 32px)

## Micro-interactions
- Add subtle animations for button clicks and transitions
- Implement visual feedback for user actions
- Keep animations short and purposeful (300-500ms)

## Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient contrast between text and background
- Use semantic widgets for better accessibility
- Support system text scaling

## Navigation
- Implement intuitive and user-friendly navigation
- Use clear visual indicators for current screen
- Provide back buttons for nested screens

## Responsive Design
- Design UI to adapt to different screen sizes
- Test layouts on both small and large devices
- Use flexible widgets like Expanded and Flexible

Always prioritize user experience and follow these principles to create a polished, engaging app.